  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zero Waste in My School (ZWMS)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Mexico, the lack of environmental public policies keeps dragging the country down into a severe crisis arising from the inappropriate handling of waste and residues.  This, without a doubt, has its origin in the school system. Also, it has been severely affected by the new structural reforms that have neglected the environmental topic and the possibility of a better education regarding waste and residue handling.  The best way to get to the root of the problem, is at school.</narrative>
  </description>
